# Playwright Standards

## Structure

- Page objects in `playwright/pages/` (TypeScript) — specs never contain raw selectors
- Auth setup in `auth.setup.ts` as a dedicated setup project
- Reusable auth fixture in `playwright/fixtures/auth.fixture.ts`
- API helpers in `playwright/utils/apiClient.ts`
- Generated auth state in `.auth/` — gitignored
- Package overview: `playwright/README.md`

## Auth

- Setup project authenticates seeded user via API → `storageState` in `.auth/user.json`
- Browser projects declare `dependencies: ['setup']`
- `auth.fixture.ts` registers unique users per test (mirrors Cypress `cy.session()`)
- Register/login specs use `chromium-unauth` project (no saved storageState)

## Selectors

- Follow ADR-003: `getByRole` → `getByLabel` → `getByPlaceholder` → `getByText`
- Selectors live in page objects only

## Reporting

- Allure via `allure-playwright` reporter in `playwright.config.ts`
- Results output to `playwright/reports/allure-results/`

## Documentation

- TSDoc on all exports in `utils/`, `fixtures/`, and `auth.setup.ts`
- TSDoc class header on each page object; method docs for composite or non-obvious behavior
- Document subtle helpers (e.g. React controlled-field input in `EditorPage`)
- No TSDoc on spec files — see `.cursor/rules/general.mdc`

## Conventions

- Specs: `tests/**/*.spec.ts`
- Run: `npm test` from `playwright/` (requires Conduit up — see package README)
- CI: `npx playwright test --retries=0`
